<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4699] Observable List misbehaves when using retainAll with closure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4699</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;List liste = new ObservableList&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;()&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;liste.add &quot;test&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
liste.add &quot;test2&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;List andereListe = new LinkedList&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;()&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;liste.retainAll &lt;/p&gt;
{ elem -&amp;gt; andereListe.contains(elem) }

&lt;p&gt;assert liste.isEmpty()&lt;br/&gt;
____________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in:&lt;br/&gt;
____________________________________________&lt;br/&gt;
Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; Assertion failed: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;assert liste.isEmpty()&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;     false&lt;br/&gt;
       &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;test&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
____________________________________________&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If the ObservableList is changed to LinkedList, the testcase works. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
